case called at 8:41am. [MK]
Defendant Jasmine A Weiss in court with Attorney Brian Severson.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Attorney Severson indicates that he did review the NGI report and discussed it with Ms. Weiss, and at this point the Defense is withdrawing the NGI Plea, maintaining the Not Guilty plea and intending to pursue case settlement negotiations.
After confirming with Ms. Weiss individually that it is her decision to withdraw the NGI plea, the Court accepts the Defense withdrawl of the NGI Plea.
The Court cites the age of this case that involves a child; the Court refers the case to Branch III for the possible scheduling of a Jury Trial. 
The Court verifies with Attorney Severson that he is satisfied with the discovery that the State has provided, though Attorney Severson notes that he anticipates receiving an update on the medical status if the doctor is going to be testifying at the trial. 
The Court indicates that it will propose that Branch III schedule the trial in March, with the Court's expectation that this will provide ample time for the parties to be prepared for trial.
Ms. Weiss verifies that the Lincoln Street, Janesville address is current.
